==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Longirostres
<hw>Lon`gi*ros"tres</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. L. <ets>longus</ets> long + <ets>rostrum</ets> beak.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A group of birds characterized by having long
slender bills, as the sandpipers, curlews, and ibises. It is now
regarded as an artificial division.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Longish</ent>⟦br⟧
